description: Fast440 is pleased to offer this Oldsmobile Cutlass S Convertible equipped with a 350 Rocket V-8/2BBL, 3-Speed Manual Transmission, Bucket Seats and Console and Power Steering/Brakes and Top. This High Quality driver features recently applied Clear Coat Paint work over straight Body Panels and  mild custom Upholstery work. The Convertible Top has been replaced and needs to be adjusted and re-stretched by a professional. Certainly a very presentable car at this price and a tremendous value. Muscle Car Convertible looks at this price ?

Mechanics are strong, the Rocket Motor has been rebuilt at some point in the car's life, runs smooth, does not smoke and no strange noises. At the very least the Transmission has been refreshed, all synchros are good, linkage is tight and shifts with authority. Other work includes Suspension and Brake work as well as a Steering Box replacement. Certainly a reliable and go anywhere car with great road manners and driving impressions. Electricals function as they should, and the car will pass your local Safety Inspection. Heater has been disconnected for either Summer driving to keep the Interior cooler or the need for a Heater Core replacement, not sure which.

The Undercarriage is solid with the exception of one small area on the Driver rear Floor Pan that has been patched. Everywhere else looks good. The Trunk Pan has been replaced. functional but not the best Craftsmanship in this area.
Again a tremendous value in a Classic Convertible. Muscle Car looks for well under 15k ? Here it is, and great foundation if you want to take it to the next level.

HISTORY:  â€œThe Oldsmobile 88 (known from 1989 onwards as the Eighty Eight) is a full-size car that was sold and produced by Oldsmobile from 1949 until 1999. From 1950 to 1974 the 88 was the division's top-selling line, particularly the entry-level models such as the 88 and Dynamic 88. The 88 series was also an image leader for Oldsmobile, particularly in the early years (1949-51) when it was one of the best performing automobiles thanks to its relatively small size, light weight and advanced overhead-valve high-compression V8 engine. This engine, originally designed for the larger C-bodied and more luxurious 98 series, also replaced the straight-8 on the smaller B-bodied 78. With the large, high performance V8, the Oldsmobile 88 is widely considered to be the first muscle car, although this title is disputed. A large number of variations in nomenclature were seen over this long model run â€” Futuramic, Super, Golden Rocket, Dynamic, Jetstar, Delta, Delmont, Starfire, Holiday, L/S, LSS, Celebrity, and Royale were used at various times with the 88 badge, and Fiesta appeared on some station wagons in the 1950s and 1960s. The name was more commonly shown as numbers in the earlier years ("Delta 88", for example) and was changed to spell-out "Eighty Eight" starting in 1989.â€-Wikipedia     SPECIFICS / BUILD INFORMATION   EXTERIOR:  -One repaint.  -New convertible top!
